261
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:39,233
The breakfast we brought
might be wasted.

262
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:39,900
- Right, Bro?
- Yes!

263
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:40,667
Why don't you join us?

264
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,900
- Come on, feel at home!
- Yes!

265
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:44,133
Come on, come on, come on!

266
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:48,467
Come on, let's grant
their request.

267
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:54,767
The party drugs are getting out
of hand these days, aren't they?

268
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,733
My God, they're even
targeting teenagers.

269
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:00,600
Well, yeah,

270
00:13:00,967 --> 00:13:03,167
it's not like they're going
to target someone

271
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:04,167
as old as the captain.

272
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:05,267
Do you think anyone will buy it?

273
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,400
You know, you're not
even thinking.

274
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:09,267
Please, Abdul?

275
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,533
My God, just for once,
can I talk to you properly?

276
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:12,767
Just for once.

277
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:13,833
No.

278
00:13:13,967 --> 00:13:15,200
I'll knock you off the tricycle.
You're annoying.

279
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,733
It's not going to happen.

280
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:19,100
Just kidding!
Come on. Don't be mad.

281
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,667
That will lighten your skin.

282
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,767
It comes with a toner,
sunscreen...

283
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:24,767
Beauty products?

284
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:26,400
Beauty products...

285
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:27,600
Even if you're already
light-skinned,

286
00:13:27,733 --> 00:13:28,567
you'll become even lighter.

287
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,533
I smell something fishy.

288
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:31,500
Let's go.

289
00:13:31,633 --> 00:13:32,333
Hey!

290
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:33,867
Just a moment.

291
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,767
What are you selling?

292
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:38,067
Beauty products.

293
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:40,467
Beauty products?

294
00:13:41,067 --> 00:13:41,667
Yes.

295
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,333
Do you sell pimple patches?

296
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:44,867
Yes.

297
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:45,867
Why?

298
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,700
We're village guards here.

299
00:13:48,233 --> 00:13:48,767
Let me see.

300
00:13:51,067 --> 00:13:52,000
Hey!

301
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:52,767
Quick!

302
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:01,300
You're so fast, girl!

303
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:02,333
Hey!

304
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:03,100
Stop!

305
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,100
Stop!

306
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:08,800
Abdul, I told you that we should
go to the gym!

307
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:11,733
No! Mar, I'm sending a lot
of people to school.

308
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:12,833
You want me to add more
to my expenses?

309
00:14:12,967 --> 00:14:14,000
My God.

310
00:14:14,133 --> 00:14:16,400
Let's skip the coffee runs
every weekend.

311
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:18,633
We can't catch up
with that witch!

312
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:20,300
Coffee is delicious!

313
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:21,400
What?

314
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:23,400
We're really going to talk
about this now, Mar?

315
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:26,367
Are you serious?
In the middle of a chase?

316
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,267
Here it is. We're sure
you'll like this, Boss.

317
00:14:29,433 --> 00:14:30,867
- Oh my, of course. There.
- What's that?

318
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,133
You'll definitely like it.

319
00:14:32,267 --> 00:14:33,333
Here it is. That's delicious,
so delicious.

320
00:14:33,467 --> 00:14:34,500
Naked spring roll.

321
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:35,333
What's that?

322
00:14:35,467 --> 00:14:36,967
Why are you covering your eyes?

323
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:39,867
Because when someone is naked,
you should cover your eyes?

324
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,033
Right, Ma'am Bobby?
Am I right?

325
00:14:41,167 --> 00:14:43,333
- Let's cover our eyes.
- Yes.

326
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:44,267
Yes, of course.

327
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,200
There.

328
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:46,500
If you don't want this,
Ma'am Bobby,

329
00:14:46,633 --> 00:14:48,767
we have a jumbo hotdog here.

330
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:51,133
Bro, there are only
three hotdogs.

331
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:52,200
There are four of us here.

332
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:54,933
Boss Tonyo, we'll open
your fridge, okay?

333
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:56,800
So we can get some
more food ready.

334
00:14:56,933 --> 00:14:57,967
Come on, Bro, let's take a look!

335
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:58,700
Let's take a look at his fridge.

336
00:14:58,833 --> 00:15:00,200
This, this. What's in here?

337
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,300
<i>- There!
- This one.</i>

338
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:06,567
<i>Ma'am Bobby, do you want
Boss Tonyo's cheesedog?</i>

339
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,867
<i>- That's delicious, cheesedog.
- That's delicious.</i>

340
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,900
<i>Ma'am Bobby, there's skinless
longganisa here too.</i>

341
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:14,367
<i> Oh, it's fat and reddish too.</i>

342
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,933
<i>You'll definitely like this,
Ma'am Bobby.</i>

343
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:17,867
<i> Sir Tonyo's footlong.</i>

344
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,400
<i> Oh, it's long!</i>

345
00:15:20,567 --> 00:15:22,300
<i>- It's so long!
- This is okay!</i>

346
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:23,433
I'm okay with this!

347
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:25,400
- This is okay!
- Stop it, you two.

348
00:15:25,533 --> 00:15:26,533
Come here.

349
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,067
- I'm okay with this.
- Are you sure?

350
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,067
Boss Tonyo, your eggs are white.

351
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,300
That's delicious.

352
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,000
You really don't like it?

353
00:15:33,633 --> 00:15:36,667
But I saw another one, Boss,
the other egg you have is red.

354
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,867
That's good for fried rice,
right?

355
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:40,233
Is that salty?

356
00:15:40,367 --> 00:15:41,633
That's okay...

357
00:15:41,767 --> 00:15:43,267
No need for the salted duck egg.
I'm okay with this.

358
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,833
No. Boss' egg looks salty,
right?

359
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:47,367
This naked spring roll
is delicious.

360
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,667
Naked again?

361
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,200
Okay.

362
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,300
Try the naked spring roll, Bro.

363
00:15:51,433 --> 00:15:52,700
Isn't that your favorite?

364
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:56,567
Is she a kangaroo?

365
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:59,033
Hey, witch! Can you please stop?

366
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,867
Why are you chasing me?

367
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,933
I'm not doing anything wrong.

368
00:16:07,067 --> 00:16:09,367
Of course, you ran.
You're crazy.

369
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:10,700
Yeah.

370
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:11,633
Wait.

371
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:12,900
Where do you go to the gym?

372
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:15,433
And how long do you spend
on the treadmill?

373
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:17,300
I don't go to the gym.

374
00:16:17,733 --> 00:16:21,233
But the things you were selling
to the teens earlier,

375
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:22,300
they were drugs, right?

376
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,733
I wasn't selling any drugs.

377
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:27,267
I had nothing to do with that.

378
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,333
So why did you run?

379
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,400
Because I was scared.

380
00:16:33,533 --> 00:16:35,967
You said you were
the village guards.

381
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:38,100
I sell fake beauty products,

382
00:16:38,233 --> 00:16:41,300
but they're good quality
and cheap.

383
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:42,467
Are you sure?

384
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,800
Yes. Check it out. Look.

385
00:16:43,933 --> 00:16:45,333
- Okay, let's see.
- Let's see.

386
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:48,033
- Buy one, take one.
- Oh my God! I have this!

387
00:16:48,167 --> 00:16:49,033
Perfect!

388
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:50,633
I bought it before
on the marketplace.

389
00:16:50,767 --> 00:16:52,133
- Do you accept credit?
- Sure.

390
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:53,400
Perfect!

391
00:16:53,533 --> 00:16:55,700
Girl, you're so greedy when
it comes to things like that.

392
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:57,200
- Hey, I like this product.
- Yes, that's nice.

393
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:59,300
But you run so fast.

394
00:16:59,433 --> 00:17:00,867
You sell so fast, too.

395
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:01,800
Yes, that's right!

396
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:03,233
Boss Tonyo!

397
00:17:03,367 --> 00:17:05,400
We'll go ahead. Thank you, Boss.

398
00:17:05,533 --> 00:17:07,267
- Thank you, Boss.
- Thank you.

399
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,000
- Ma'am Bobby!
- Take care!

400
00:17:09,133 --> 00:17:10,300
Thank you!

401
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:11,933
- I hope you eat the hotdog.
- Thank you for the breakfast.

402
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:12,867
- No worries!
- Take care!

403
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:20,133
Sir Tonyo...

404
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:21,300
- Leave it there.
- Where am I going to put this?

405
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:22,267
Okay.

406
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,867
There's still some more.
This is delicious.

407
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:32,233
Sir, there's something
on your...

408
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,167
<i> You have a big build, Sir.</i>

409
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,333
<i> We're okay, right?</i>

410
00:18:06,967 --> 00:18:07,767
<i> Us?</i>

411
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,967
<i>Your clothes look good
on you too.</i>

412
00:18:35,467 --> 00:18:36,567
Thank you, Miss.

413
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,100
In fairness to her...

414
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,700
her fake items are legit, right?

415
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:43,733
Are you crazy?

416
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:45,467
Legit, and then fake?

417
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,467
You're talking nonsense, Abdul.

418
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:49,033
What do you mean by nonsense?

419
00:18:49,467 --> 00:18:51,100
You're the one who brought up
the gym

420
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:53,133
while we were chasing her.

421
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:54,067
Hey.

422
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:56,500
Captain...

423
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,900
Hey, Captain, I noticed...

424
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,333
you've been on your cell phone
for a while now.

425
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,933
It looks like you're waiting
for a text or call.

426
00:19:06,067 --> 00:19:07,800
Oh, I know it already.

427
00:19:08,633 --> 00:19:11,267
She's meeting someone.

428
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,500
Captain, have you joined
a dating app yet?

429
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,633
Swipe left, right.

430
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:17,033
- Right?
- I used to swipe right a lot.

431
00:19:17,167 --> 00:19:17,867
Oh, yeah.

432
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,400
I chatted with lot
of people there.

433
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,367
I know that.

434
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:21,600
Stop bothering me.

435
00:19:22,633 --> 00:19:24,167
What if I slap your faces
with my shoes?

436
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:26,267
The sole is thick, see.

437
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:28,800
That's it.

438
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:32,533
But, Captain,
why don't you call Bobby?

439
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:34,800
I know you miss her, too, right?

440
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:35,867
- She hasn't come home yet.
- Yeah.

441
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,367
Yes, Captain.
Don't you have any load?

442
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,300
- I'll send you a load.
- Or connect to my hotspot.

443
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:42,133
I have some extra gigs left.

444
00:19:42,633 --> 00:19:43,733
What's happening?
Captain is getting poor.

445
00:19:43,867 --> 00:19:45,200
You connected to my hotspot
earlier, right?

446
00:19:45,567 --> 00:19:46,533
You're so shameless.

447
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,867
Hotspot, just connect
to my phone.

448
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,267
Captain!

449
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:56,100
You look bad in your picture.
Let's change it.

450
00:19:56,633 --> 00:19:57,100
Abdul...

451
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:57,800
She doesn't look good...

452
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:01,867
Captain is still affected
by her fight with Bobby.

453
00:20:02,767 --> 00:20:05,800
But we know they can't ignore
each other.

454
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:07,000
They'll eventually patch
things up.

455
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:10,067
I agree, but I hope
Booby goes home.

456
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,100
You're right.

457
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:12,367
Because Captain Isang
will take it out on us.

458
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:13,333
Correct!

459
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:15,200
Didn't you see those heels?
They're thick.

460
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:16,867
My beauty will be ruined
by that.

461
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,433
What if that's the one we bring
while patrolling the streets?

462
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:20,433
And for strolling too.

463
00:20:20,567 --> 00:20:22,033
Besides, it's scary to look at,
isn't it?

464
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,167
- Yes.
- That's right.

465
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,167
I like that. We can use it
when we go for stroll.

466
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:26,200
But you know, it looks ugly.

467
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,400
I think that's Lee and Bal.

468
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,567
Wrong timing.

469
00:21:04,433 --> 00:21:06,100
What do you need?

470
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:09,700
Selena...

471
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:12,633
What are you doing here?

472
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:14,867
Sir Tonyo, I need your help.

473
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:18,667
Ma'am Bobby,
what are you doing here?

474
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:26,100
We had a police operation
last night.

475
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:31,133
We finished late, so Bobby
slept in the living room.

476
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:37,900
Why are you carrying a suitcase,
and what help do you need?

477
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,167
Well, Sir Tonyo...

478
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,667
I haven't been able to pay
the rent.

479
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:46,433
Well, you know, I haven't been
able to work

480
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:49,867
because I'm busy being a witness
in Amo's case.

481
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:52,700
I've been kicked out.

482
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:57,867
If it's not too much trouble,
maybe I could stay here...

483
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,300
for a long time?

484
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:01,867
For a long time?

485
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:03,600
For a short time.

486
00:22:03,733 --> 00:22:05,300
Just kidding.
You're too serious.

487
00:22:05,767 --> 00:22:08,933
I promise, I'll leave
when I find a new job.

488
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:11,267
Whatever you need, I'll do it.

489
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,033
If you need a cleaner, a cook...

490
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:17,167
If you want, Sir Tonyo,
I'll massage you every night.

491
00:22:17,667 --> 00:22:19,500
Selena, I'm sorry...

492
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:21,333
Selena, it's a good thing
that you came here.

493
00:22:21,767 --> 00:22:25,300
You know that Sir Tonyo
won't refuse you.

494
00:22:26,333 --> 00:22:27,133
Really?

495
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:28,933
Oh my, thank you very much.

496
00:22:29,067 --> 00:22:31,200
Your house is beautiful,
Sir Tonyo.

497
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:32,700
Looks cozy.

498
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:35,367
Sir, I'll go ahead.

499
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,267
Bobby...

500
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:42,300
Sir Tonyo, where can I put
my things?

501
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:44,333
Will we stay together
in the room?

502
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:48,467
- I'm getting hungry.
- I want to eat too.

503
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,633
Right?

504
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:50,800
- Where should we eat?
- I don't know.

505
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:52,100
Good day, Captain.

506
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:52,833
Captain...

507
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:53,800
Let's go.

508
00:22:55,033 --> 00:22:58,833
You know, Mar,
Bobby's job is hard, right?

509
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:01,767
Oh, yes, you're right.

510
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:03,733
Especially when they conduct
a police operation.

511
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,700
One of her feet is in the grave.

512
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:10,000
Oh my, it's scary.
But you know what's scarier?

513
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:12,700
What if something bad happens
to Bobby?

514
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:15,967
She and Captain Isang are not
okay. Isn't that harder?

515
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:18,333
My God, you're right!

516
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:21,500
Oh my, they'll both regret it.

517
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,967
Nothing bad will happen
to Bobby!

518
00:23:25,033 --> 00:23:27,800
We know that, Captain.

519
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:32,167
Well, our point is that
the future is uncertain.

520
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:37,400
That's why it's better if you
don't prolong the fights,

521
00:23:37,533 --> 00:23:40,167
especially with the ones
you love, right?

522
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:41,133
Yes.

523
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:44,600
And Captain, you're Bobby's
only family.

524
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:47,367
What if you get kidnapped again?

525
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,767
We can't save you.

526
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:52,167
What about Bobby?
She'll be all alone.

527
00:23:52,833 --> 00:23:54,400
Poor Bobby.

528
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,467
She'll be an orphan while you
have a misunderstanding.

529
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:58,367
Why?

530
00:23:59,567 --> 00:24:01,567
Because you don't want
to let her join

531
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,900
the mayor's task force
in Calabari.

532
00:24:04,033 --> 00:24:05,333
Why, Captain?

533
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:06,133
Why?

534
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:07,500
Oh my God!

535
00:24:07,767 --> 00:24:09,367
You're so petty, Captain!

536
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:13,433
What a shame, what a shame...

537
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:18,433
Bobby texted.

538
00:24:18,567 --> 00:24:19,767
What did she say?

539
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:23,767
"I'm on my way home.
Has grandmother eaten yet?"

540
00:24:24,867 --> 00:24:26,867
"Please tell her
to take her medicine."

541
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,533
Look!

542
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,133
Bobby's still thinking
about you!

543
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:33,267
What a shame, Captain.

544
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,667
What a shame...

545
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:35,833
What a shame...

546
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:37,767
<i> That's how we are.</i>

547
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,067
<i> When we wake up,</i>

548
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:42,433
<i>we look fresh and beautiful
because that's in our genes.</i>

549
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:44,167
Yes.

550
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:46,033
- Are you ashamed?
- My name is Shame.

551
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:47,733
I am ashamed.

552
00:24:47,867 --> 00:24:48,833
No, you're not.

553
00:25:01,433 --> 00:25:02,533
You're here already.

554
00:25:03,867 --> 00:25:04,467
Grandmother...

555
00:25:04,967 --> 00:25:06,400
I was so worried about you.

556
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:08,500
I wish you had texted me.

557
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:10,867
Grandmother, I'm sorry.

558
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:15,467
We had a police operation
last night,

559
00:25:15,967 --> 00:25:18,200
the one I told you about,
the pimple patch.

560
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:21,200
Sorry, Grandmother,
I just got home today.

561
00:25:22,633 --> 00:25:23,700
I was really worried.

562
00:25:25,467 --> 00:25:27,133
But I have something
to tell you.

563
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:30,467
- Grandchild, I'm sorry.
- Grandmother...

564
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:32,367
you're right.

565
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:35,600
I can still do all my work

566
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:39,167
even if I don't join the mayor's
special task force.

567
00:25:41,167 --> 00:25:43,500
Do you know what's more
important to me?

568
00:25:44,767 --> 00:25:45,500
You.

569
00:25:49,133 --> 00:25:52,100
So if we're just going to fight
about this, there's no need.

570
00:25:52,233 --> 00:25:54,100
I'll just decline it.

571
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:58,900
Because you're the most
important thing to me.

572
00:26:00,167 --> 00:26:01,567
I love you, Grandmother.

573
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:02,633
I love you.

574
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:12,167
Grandchild, I have something
to tell you.

575
00:26:13,833 --> 00:26:14,933
What is it?

576
00:26:15,067 --> 00:26:18,800
You already know that your
mother was rejected by the man

577
00:26:18,933 --> 00:26:20,400
who got her pregnant?

578
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,533
Yes, Grandmother. Why?

579
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:30,067
Because the one who got her
pregnant is Mayor Guerrero!

580
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:41,433
I'll admit something to you.
I've cheated on your mother.

581
00:26:41,567 --> 00:26:42,400
What?

582
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:45,067
Study your identities.
Take it to heart.

583
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,733
For people to believe you,

584
00:26:46,867 --> 00:26:48,400
you have to be the first
to believe.

585
00:26:48,533 --> 00:26:49,633
Where are these two?

586
00:26:49,767 --> 00:26:50,600
They're at the gym, Bro.

587
00:26:50,733 --> 00:26:51,933
This is the first time
I saw your faces!

588
00:26:52,067 --> 00:26:52,867
What do you want?

589
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:54,367
We just want to see
how good you are.

590
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:55,033
Bobby got promoted?

591
00:26:55,167 --> 00:26:55,933
Yes, Bok.

592
00:26:56,067 --> 00:26:58,000
Not just here at
the police station.

593
00:26:58,133 --> 00:26:58,667
Where else?

594
00:26:58,800 --> 00:26:59,833
In your heart.

595
00:26:59,967 --> 00:27:02,400
We are here at the clubhouse

596
00:27:02,533 --> 00:27:06,400
because today we will witness
a friendly swimming race

597
00:27:06,533 --> 00:27:08,500
between two competent
police women,

598
00:27:08,633 --> 00:27:10,067
Lieutenant Charlie Samson

599
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:15,200
and, of course,
Sergeant Bobby Enriquez!
